text: Qikiqtagafaaluk formerly Admiralty IslandQikiqtagafaaluk (formerly Admiralty Island) is an uninhabited, irregularly shaped Arctic island in the Kitikmeot Region of Nunavut, Canada. It is located in the Victoria Strait, south of Victoria Island's Collinson Peninsula. ==References== Category:Victoria Island (Canada) Category:Islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago Category:Uninhabited islands of Kitikmeot Region Category:Islands of Kitikmeot Region
